From: Srinivasa Rao Mandadapu <quic_srivasam@quicinc.com>
Date: Tue, 22 Nov 2022 12:01:13 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: soc-pcm: Add NULL check in BE reparenting
Git-commit: db8f91d424fe0ea6db337aca8bc05908bbce1498
Patch-mainline: v6.1-rc7
References: CVE-2022-48992 bsc#1232071

Add NULL check in dpcm_be_reparent API, to handle
kernel NULL pointer dereference error.
The issue occurred in fuzzing test.

Signed-off-by: Srinivasa Rao Mandadapu <quic_srivasam@quicinc.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/1669098673-29703-1-git-send-email-quic_srivasam@quicinc.com
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 sound/soc/soc-pcm.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/sound/soc/soc-pcm.c
+++ b/sound/soc/soc-pcm.c
@@ -1168,6 +1168,8 @@ static void dpcm_be_reparent(struct snd_
 		return;
 
 	be_substream = snd_soc_dpcm_get_substream(be, stream);
+	if (!be_substream)
+		return;
 
 	list_for_each_entry(dpcm, &be->dpcm[stream].fe_clients, list_fe) {
 		if (dpcm->fe == fe)
